<h2 id=3D"AccessPointAIApplication-Corecomponentsandworkflow">Core componen=
ts and workflow</h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>User interface and natural language processing (NLP)</strong></p=
></li>
</ol>
<p>The process begins with the user interface AccesspointAI, which allows e=
mployees to submit requests using natural, everyday language. This interfac=
e can be a custom chatbot integrated into a messaging platform (like Slack =
or Microsoft Teams), a web portal, or a virtual assistant.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Request submission:</strong> An employee asks for access to a sp=
ecific application or resource, for example, "I need access to Salesforce f=
or my new role".</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Intent recognition:</strong> The AccessPointAI uses NLP to under=
stand the user's intent. It identifies key entities such as the user's name=
, the requested application, and the reason for the request.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2">
<li>
<p><strong>AccesspointAI and machine learning (ML) engine</strong><br>
This component is the core of the application, where the AccesspointAI proc=
esses the user's request.</p></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Data gathering and enrichment:</strong> The AI connects to vario=
us data sources, such as the organization's Human Resources Information Sys=
tem (HRIS) or Active Directory, to gather additional information about the =
employee, including their job role, department, and manager.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Decision-making:</strong> The ML model uses this contextual info=
rmation to determine the appropriate access levels. It can predict what per=
missions a user needs based on their role and compare it to peer group acce=
ss patterns to ensure consistency and security.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Automated approval (optional):</strong> For low-risk or common r=
equests, the AI can automatically approve the access request without human =
intervention. For higher-risk requests, it can route the request to the app=
ropriate manager or owner for approval via a messaging platform or ticketin=
g system.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3">
<li>
<p><strong>Integration and provisioning engine</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p><br>
Once the AI has processed and approved the request, it sends a command to t=
he provisioning application.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>API integration:</strong> The AI application sends a request to =
the provisioning system's API. This is done programmatically to ensure accu=
racy and speed.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Account provisioning:</strong> The provisioning system, often an=
 identity and access management (IAM) tool like Microsoft Entra ID (formerl=
y Azure AD), executes the request by automatically creating, updating, or d=
eleting user accounts and assigning the correct access rights across the ta=
rget systems.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Status update:</strong> The provisioning system communicates the=
 status of the request back to the AI application.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"4">
<li>
<p><strong>User notification</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p><br>
The AI application informs the user and other stakeholders about the reques=
t's status.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Confirmation:</strong> The user receives a message confirming th=
at their request has been processed and access has been granted.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Audit trail:</strong> An audit log is updated to provide a clear=
, trackable record of all provisioning activities, which is crucial for sec=
urity and compliance.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"AccessPointAIApplication-Keybenefits">Key benefits</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Faster onboarding:</strong> New employees can get access to the =
tools they need on day one, significantly improving their productivity.</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Reduced IT workload:</strong> The IT team is freed from repetiti=
ve, manual provisioning tasks and can focus on more strategic, high-value p=
rojects.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Enhanced security:</strong> Automated provisioning enforces the =
principle of least privilege, ensuring users only have the access they need=
. It also provides an immediate and automatic process for deprovisioning, r=
educing the risk of unauthorized access when an employee leaves the company=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Improved compliance:</strong> A clear audit trail of all access =
requests and changes helps meet regulatory compliance requirements and prov=
ides visibility into the process.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Better user experience:</strong> The self-service, conversationa=
l interface makes it easy for employees to request the resources they need.=
&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
